headline: Southwest Airlines adds a policy Delta and United passengers hate
summary: In late January, Southwest Airlines ended its decades-long open seating policy, moving to assigned seats in a bid to boost revenue from extra-legroom and priority boarding options. The change also reshaped how the airline manages boarding, baggage, and on-time performance, highlighting the fine ...

headline: From AI Darlings To Dow Dinosaurs: Investors Flee Software For Old-Economy Stocks
summary: Software stocks are sliding as AI disruption fears grow, but investors aren't panicking. Goldman Sachs shows capital rotating toward AI-insulated, real-economy sectors.

headline: Pressure mounts on American Airlines CEO as carrier lags rivals
summary: American Airlines made $111 million last year, while rivals Delta Air Lines and United Airlines, brought in $5 billion and $3.3 billion, respectively.
